div.p:
Missa Elisabeth Zachariae (4vv)
92 MISSA ELISABETH ZACHARIAE. iiij. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRUCE√ëA. 93. Kyrie, Gloria, and Credo: missing.
Sanctus ([86]-[89]): Superius and Tenor missing; small losses from Altus and Bassus; Osanna in ÔÅ¶3/2.
The upper outside quadrant of pp. 87-88 survives, detatched from the book. Most of the Altus and some of the Bassus is preserved on p. 87 while most of the Superius and some of the Tenor is preserved on p. 88. A small fragment of the outer side of pp. [89]-[90] survives, detatched from the binding. It preserves some notes from the Bassus of the Sanctus and the Tenor of the Benedictus.
Benedictus ([90]-91): 3vv (SAT), Altus complete; Superius missing, significant losses from Tenor.
Agnus (92-3): Superius, Altus, and Tenor complete; Bassus lacks most of final stave.
Source motet: Francisco Guerrero, Elisabeth Zacharaiae (secunda pars: Dominus ab utero) 5vv (SSTTB) from Mottetta (Venice: Filio Antonii Gardani, 1570) [RISM G4871], no. 48 and Motecta (Venice: Giacomo Vincenti, 1597) [RISM G4877], no. 47.

94 MISSA QVE PROGREDITVR. iiij. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRVCE√ëA. 95

Gloria (100-107): Superius complete; minor losses from Altus, Tenor and Bassus.

Sanctus (118-119): complete.
Benedictus (120-121): 3vv (SAB), complete.
Agnus (122-123): complete.
Source motet: Giovanni Pierluigi da Palestrina, Quae es ista quae progreditur 5vv (SSTTB) from Motettorum quinque vocibus liber quartus (Rome: Alessandro Gardano, 1584) [Tenor and Bassus, 1583; Superius, Altus, and Quintus, 1584] [RISM P716], no. 23.

124 MISSA TV ES PARTOR [sic] OVIVM. iiij. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRVCE√ëA. 125

Gloria (126-129): Superius and Altus complete; significant losses from Tenor, minor losses from Bassus.

Source motet: Giovanni Pierluigi da Palestrina, Tu es pastor ovium 4vv (SATB), from Motecta festorum totius anni liber primus (Venice: Antonio Gardano, 1564) [RISM P689], no. 14.

div.p: The ornamented 'Q' is the first word of the hymn, 'Quia.' Each section of the choir in the book begins with the same ornamented letter.
You can comment on text that wasn't transcribed via hotspots.

Tribulationes cordis mea (6vv)
252 PRO QVACVNQVE NECESSITATE. vj. vocu[m]. // DIDACVS DE BRVCE√ëA. 253
Motet (SSAATB), all voices complete.
TRibulationes cordis mei dilatate sunt, De necessitatibus meis, eripe me Domine vide humilitatem meam & laborem meum, & dimite omnia peccata mea. (Psalm 24: 17-18).

256 COMVNE APOSTOLORVM. vj. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRVCE√ëA. 257
Motet (SSAATB), all voices complete.
HOc est pr√¶ceptum meum, vt diligatis inuicem sicut dilexi vos. Maiorem charitatem nemo habet, vt animam suam ponat quis pro amicis suis. (John 15: 12-13).

260 COMVNE VNIVS MARTIRIS. vj. vocu[m]. // DIDACVS DE BRVCE√ëA. 261
Motet (SSAATB), all voices complete.
ISte sanctus pro lege Dei sui, certauit vsque ad mortem, & √† verbis impiorum non timuit fundatus enim erat supra firmam petram. (Antiphon at the magnificat, common of a martyr).

264 DE VEATA VIRGINE. vj. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRVCE√ëA. 265
Motet (SSAATB), all voices complete. Words tu singularis set in ÔÉÜ3/2. S1 and S2 have ÔÉã3/2 in error.
AVe sanctissima Maria. Mater Dei, Regina c≈ìli, Porta Paradisi, Domina mundi, tu singularis pura es Virgo tu Concepisti lesum sine peccato, libera me ab omni malo, & ora pro peccatis meis. (Marian devotional antiphon, Breviarum Romanum completissimum [Venice: Lucantonio Giunta, 1522] f. 23v.

270 DE BEATA VIRGINE. vj. [sic] vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRVCE√ëA. 271
Motet (SSATB), all voices complete.
STabat mater dolorosa,
iusta crucem lachrimosa,
dum pendebat Filius.
Cuius animam gemente[m],
Contristantem & dolentem
pertransiuit gladius.
√≤ quam tristis & aflicta
fuit illa benedicta,
mater vnigeniti. (Sequence extract).

282 In transfiguracione Domini. iiij. vocum. // DIDACVS DE BRVCE√ëA. 281 [recte 283]

The first note in the fourth stave of the Tenor has been corrected by hand to F sharp.
